        "synopsis": {
            "value": "As Shim Su-Ryeon (Lee Ji-Ah) walks to the parking lot to meet Logan Lee (Park Eun-Seok), an explosion takes place by his car. A suspicious elderly man walks by, while a mysterious figure watches in the background.\n\nOnce the residents from Hera Place are released from prison, Shim Su-Ryeon and Oh Yoon-Hee (Eugene) form an alliance with Cheon Seo-Jin (Kim So-Yeon) to take down Joo Dan-Tae (Uhm Ki-Joon). Soon, Baek Joon-Ki (On Joo-Wan) enters the picture as an old friend of Joo Dan-Tae. What secret does he hold on Joo Dan-Tae? Meanwhile, Yoo Dong-Pil (Park Ho-San), husband of Kang Ma-Ri (Shin Eun-Kyung) and father of Yoo Je-Ni (Jin Ji-Hee), returns to Hera Place after spending six years away. He seethes inside and seeks revenge on Joo Dan-Tae. At Cheong-A Arts School, Joo Seok-Kyung (Han Ji-Hyun) faces punishment for her past bullying actions.",
